translated:
Malmöh. 1st, of the County Governor Count Gotth. W. and Baroness Elisabeth von Essen. Married in 1900 to Greta Lindström. Children: Eva born in 1900, deceased in 1947, Carl Johan born in 1903, Hans born in 1912. Graduated from Stockholm in 1890, second lieutenant of the Göta Artillery Regiment in 1893, lieutenant in 1898, captain in 1904, major of the Småland Artillery Regiment in 1916, lieutenant colonel of the Göta Artillery Regiment in 1922. Recipient of the Royal Order of the Sword, Royal Order of the North Star, Royal Order of Vasa, and Knight of the Finnish Order of the White Rose.

Hans Wilhehn, Axelsson, civil forester, count, Karlskrona, born on December 25, 1913, in Lidingö, son of the cavalry master Count Ajcel W. and Caroda von Eckermann. Married in 1938 to Ingrid Tobieson. Children: Hans born in 1940, Wilhelm born in 1942, Gabriel born in 1943, Agneta born in 1946. Graduated from Karlskrona in 1935, graduated from the Forestry School in 1938, ensign in the Life Grenadier Regiment in 1935, captain in 1945. Assistant military attaché at the embassy in Paris in 1938, fuel chief in Blekinge in 1945-1946, agricultural manager of the Johannishus fideicommissum from 1946. Knight of the Order of Vasa, Karlskrona Swordsmen's Guild Medal, 2nd Class Skytte Medal, Skytte Regiment Medal.
